[4] Pakistan, 246 cases - media report
Date: Fri 14 Nov 2014
Source: The Express Tribune [edited]
http://tribune.com.pk/story/791213/epidemic-scale-polio-count-jumps-to-246-with-three-more-cases/


Epidemic scale: Polio count jumps to 246 with 3 more cases
----------------------------------------------------------
3-day special drive starts in 11 areas declared 'super high-risk'.

3 more polio cases were reported from the Federally Administered Tribal Areas (FATA) on Friday [14 Nov 2014], taking this year's total to 246. According to officials of the health department, 2 infected children belong to Khyber Agency, while 1 child is from South Waziristan Agency. However, the details of the children could not be ascertained till this report was filed. "We have just confirmed 3 new cases from FATA, but their names and ages have not been released as yet," said a health department official, who requested anonymity.

Pakistan is now just 4 polio cases shy of reaching 250. Of the 246, 158 children are from FATA, 49 from Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa, 25 from Sindh, 11 from Balochistan and 3 from Punjab.

--
