<promed@promedmail.org>

[While the official statistics are for 236 cases of WPV-associated polio confirmed in Pakistan as of 11 Nov 2014, it appears as though an additional 10 cases have been confirmed in the 3 days since the official tally was released for this week. The breakdown of locations provided in the media report above has 158 of the 246 cases (64.2 per cent) from the FATA, 49 (19.9 per cent) from Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa, 25 (10.2 per cent) from Sindh, 11 (4.5 per cent) from Balochistan and 3 (1.2 per cent) from Punjab. According to the official figures from the Pakistan End Polio website, of the 236 WPV-associated polio cases this year to date (2014), 152 cases are from the FATA, 48 are from Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa, 23 are from Sindh, 10 are from Balochistan, and 3 are from Punjab. Hence, the 10 additional cases reflected in the above media report include 6 cases in FATA, 1 case in Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa, 2 cases in Sindh, and 1 case in Balochistan (see http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polio-in-pakistan).

For maps of Pakistan showing the locations of cases reported in 2014, see http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polio-in-pakistan, and click on each of the links on the left side of the page for total country and province by province. - Mod.MPP]

